    <div class="container">
        <h1>📘 Coding Club Test – Rules, Syllabus & Schedule</h1>

        <section>
            <h2>🛡️ Rules & Regulations</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>✅ Test duration: 60 minutes</li>
                <li>✅ Mode: Online (in college lab / classroom)</li>
                <li>✅ No use of internet, mobile phones, or external help</li>
                <li>✅ Strictly individual participation</li>
                <li>✅ Malpractice leads to disqualification</li>
                <li>✅ You must register before the deadline to be eligible</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>📚 Syllabus / Topics Covered</h2>

            <h3>👨‍💼 Section 1 – Programming Basics</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Data Types, Variables, Loops, Conditions</li>
                <li>Functions and Recursion</li>
                <li>Array and String manipulations</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>📂 Section 2 – Data Structures & Algorithms</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Stack, Queue, Linked List (Basic questions)</li>
                <li>Sorting (Bubble, Selection, Insertion)</li>
                <li>Searching Algorithms (Linear, Binary Search)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>💻 Section 3 – Debugging & Output Prediction</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Predict the output of given code snippets</li>
                <li>Find and fix errors</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>✨ Section 4 – Aptitude + Logical Reasoning (Optional)</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Basic MCQs (Time, Work, Blood Relations, etc.)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>🕒 Test Schedule</h2>
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Date</th>
                    <th>Time</th>
                    <th>Venue</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>28 April</td>
                    <td>11:00 AM</td>
                    <td>Lab 1 / Online</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>28 April</td>
                    <td>2:00 PM</td>
                    <td>Lab 2 (if overflow)</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>🎯 Evaluation Criteria</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Total Marks: 50</li>
                <li>Programming MCQs: 20 marks</li>
                <li>Coding/Debugging: 20 marks</li>
                <li>Aptitude (optional): 10 marks</li>
                <li>Top scorers will be shortlisted for next round</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>📢 Additional Instructions</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Bring your college ID card</li>
                <li>Be present 10 minutes before the test</li>
                <li>Result will be declared within 2 days on notice board & portal</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

